Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped into small pieces) into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and chopped into 2cm chunks) and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

In a large #oven dish{}, mix @prawns{150%g}, @chopped tomato with onion & garlic{1%pack}, bell pepper, half the @dried oregano{1/2%sachet}, @vegetable stock{1%sachet}, @dried chilli flakes{2%sachets} (use less if you don't like spice), onion, garlic and @water{100%ml} (per 2P). IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Season with @salt{1/2%tsp} (per 2P), @sugar{1/2%tsp} (per 2P) and @pepper{to taste}.

Place the whole block of @Greek style cheese{100%g} on top of everything.

Scatter over the remaining @dried oregano{1/2%sachet} and drizzle over a little @oil{to taste}.

Bake on the top shelf of the oven until bubbling and cooked through, ~{30-35%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @parsley{5%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

When everything is almost ready, halve the @ciabatta{2%units}(halved lengthways) lengthways then pop into the oven, cut-side up, to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide the baked prawns between #plates{}.

Sprinkle over the chopped parsley.

Serve the ciabatta alongside.